Preheat your oven to 220°C. Chop the @potato{2} into wedges about the size of your
index finger (no need to peel). Put on a #baking tray{} and drizzle over a little
@olive oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Toss to coat then roast on the
top shelf of your oven for ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

Coarsely grate the @carrot{1} and @apple{1}. Peel and grate the @beetroot{1}. Put all
three in a #mixing bowl{} and squeeze over half the @lemon{1}. Add the
@Greek style natural yoghurt{1} and mix.

> TIP: If your children aren't fans of beetroot, leave it out of the slaw and add it
> in separately for the adults at the end.

Remove the @baby gem lettuce{2} root, halve lengthways, thinly slice and put in a
small #bowl{}. Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(stalks and all).

Lay each @British chicken breasts{3} on a #chopping board{}, place your hand flat on
top and slice into it from the side so you can open it up like a book. You've now
butterflied your chicken! Chop into 1cm pieces. Put the chicken in a mixing bowl.
Add the @Mexican spice{1.5}, the remaining lemon juice and the @honey{2}. Season
with salt and black pepper and mix well.

Put a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. When hot, add the
chicken. Cook until lightly browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. If your pan is small, do this in
batches as the chicken needs to fry, not stew!

> TIP: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Once done, put the chicken in another mixing bowl. Add the coriander and stir to
combine.

Put the @super soft tortillas with whole wheat{8} in your oven to warm through for a
few minutes while you put your bowls of lettuce, slaw and chicken on the table,
along with a big plate of potato wedges!

Assemble at the table! Serve your wraps with a little @tomato mayonnaise{4}, the
chicken and some lettuce inside and have some wedges and slaw as accompaniments.
Enjoy!